title: For Sale/Trade:  PTR 91 GI Special Edition with extras
postcontent: What I have listed here is considered the cream of the crop when it comes to user friendly PTR rifles. This is a early build PTR 91 GI. Let me explain why you want this one. It's no secret that the early PTR builds featured more actual GI parts. This rifle by serial number, falls in production after the ones that experience cracks in the front trunion. It also falls before those that had a change in barrel design that prevents the shooting of most surplus 7.62x51! Why a GI model (the budget model) over say a 91F? I'll tell you! The 91 GI has a barrel profile that mimics the original HK design. That means the accuracy takes a slight hit, however it will feed damn near any ammo! The 91F while only a bit more accurate, will not fire most surplus ammo reliable! You can also add a port buffer (which this rifle has!) The 91F has a welded on top rail that prevents the addition of a port buffer. What the port buffer dose is save your brass from getting the trademark HK dent. It also keeps it from flying 30 ft away! Why am I asking 1500.00 for a used rifle that costs 995.00? Quite simply put, with everything on this rifle, it would cost you over 2k to build new! This rifle has the following upgrades, German wide handguard, HK bipod, HK Parts large charging handle (not yet installed), HK parts steel trigger housing, HK factory tuned trigger group (incredible difference in pull and take up), HK Parts sniper grip, MFI clamp on top rail (receiver is in spec, you can lift the rifle by the rail it's on that good), POF port buffer, and Magpul adjustable stock (for leangth of pull and cheek weld.) Top it off you will also get the original Navy trigger housing with trigger group, an additional HK GI style grip, 26 aluminum HK magazines, and all the original paperwork and case! Try to top this deal!

location: Far NE IL, Illinois, United States
postcontent:
Hammerli 208/International, the Grand Master of the S&W 41-type gun.  

Like the S&W41, the 208 evolved from the Walther Olympia of the 1930s, which itself was an adaptation of the Reising Target Pistol.  After an unsuccessful adaptation by Hammerli following WWII as the Hammerli Walther Olympia, the International saw the gun revised extensive with a far superior result.

Important note:  some have said the Armslist email system is NOT forwarding inquiries.  If you receive no response within a day, please email directly at REDACTED, or start by emailing directly.

The 208 is, in essence, the ultimate S&W41 that Smith and Wesson never made.

The barrel is a solid unit with the frame, with superb (close to 0.5 MOA) accuracy resulting.  The trigger is excellent for consistency, and readily adjustable from about 400 gms to about 3000.  In addition to having a "fine" adjustment, this gun offers a coarse adjustment system for rapid adjustment from heavy to light pull weights.

Gun weight can be adjusted by change in barrel weights (0-270 gm available).  The original Hammerli grip is one of the best ever offered for a handgun.

This gun includes the original box that is SN matched to the gun and one magazine.  Additional magazines (OEM Hammerli) available.

This gun has no safety.  One with a hammer block/trigger block safety also is available with 2 SN matched magazines, same price.

The images show BOTH of the guns available. One is with a SN matched box and 1 magazine, the other with 2 SN matched magazines and no box.  One has a safety, one does not.  Both have the rapid adjust for the trigger.

The aluminum parts are black anodized 6061-T6 and the steel parts are phosphate coated.  The shell ejector can be adjustment as to prevent it from rubbing the bottom of your bolt and the block can be adjusted slightly up and down to properly set the feed ramp height.  It also has a unique locking system that prevents the block from moving after adjustment.  It requires no gunsmithing and no modifications are required to your lower receiver.  It can be installed in just minutes and includes all hex wrenches (3) required to set.  It is completely adjusted to factory setting that will work on most applications without any further adjustments.
